Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Assistant Library Director - Temporary Leave Coverage Radium Hot Springs , BC Description Employment Opportunity: Assistant Library Director (Temporary Leave Coverage) Term: 13 months (up to 24 hours per week, Tuesday to Friday) Wage and Benefits:$23.20/hr plus limited benefits after 3 month probation period Start Date: Tuesday December 3, 2024End Date: January 3, 2026 Situated in the centre of the vibrant village of Radium Hot Springs, British Columbia, the Radium Hot Springs Public Library is a welcoming and inclusive community hub and meeting place. The Library is seeking an energetic, organized and personable candidate to fulfill a temporary term position as Assistant Library Director. The Assistant Library Director is responsible for overseeing the development and coordination of library programs and services according to both our library’s Mission, Vision, and Values (found at https://radium.bc.libraries.coop/library-information/strategic-plan/), and our policies and procedures (found at https://radium.bc.libraries.coop/library-information/policies/). Key tasks include: program development, facilitation, and evaluation; relationship-building with other community-based organizations; management of the mail-out interlibrary loan department; and promotion of library programs and services. The Assistant Library Director will report to the Library Director. As this position is coverage for a leave, there is the possibility of a contract extension. A strong candidate will have an understanding of the community and surrounding areas the Library serves, be able to work and interact with others from varying backgrounds and abilities, and have a passion for and experience in working with children. While prior experience working as a library programming coordinator or Assistant Library Director is ideal, a combination of alternative experience, education and local knowledge will be considered. Interested candidates are invited to email info@radium.bclibrary.ca for a full job description. To apply, please email director@radium.bclibrary.ca with a cover letter and resume on or before Tuesday, October 15, 2024. While we appreciate interest from all applicants, only those selected for an interview will be contacted. The Radium Hot Springs Public Library strives to provide appropriate accommodations to help all staff members thrive in their work and encourages applications from diverse candidates. As the Radium Hot Springs Public Library has a responsibility to provide a safe and welcoming environment for its users and employees, a vulnerable sector criminal record check is a condition of employment. Personal information collected is used in accordance with the BC Freedom of Information and Protection of Privacy Act. https://radium.bc.libraries.coop/ Compensation $23.30/hr Closes: 15 October, 2024 Radium Hot Springs Public Library Radium Hot Springs , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
