Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? PUBLIC SERVICE ASSISTANT (Casual) West Vancouver , BC Description Located on the traditional, ancestral and unceded lands of the Musqueam, Squamish, and Tsleil-Waututh Nations, West Vancouver is a vibrant community on the North Shore and home to parks, beaches, and to sports, recreation and arts amenities. We are seeking employees with a passion for public service who share our commitment to creating a complete, inclusive and livable community.The West Vancouver Memorial Library has an opening for a casual, on-call Public Service Assistant. The WVML Technology Team is passionate, inspired, and known throughout the province for innovation, responsiveness, and leadership. Reporting to the Library Services Coordinator—Digital Experience, and working alongside a motivated high-performing team, the Public Service Assistant is responsible for providing service to customers in the Community Computing Centre in person, over the phone, and via email; providing technology support to staff; and assisting with various technology related projects with potential opportunity for shifts in Youth and Customer &amp; Community Experience as well.The successful candidates will possess:Excellent interpersonal and customer service skills;Ability to communicate effectively orally and in writing;Working knowledge of PC and Mac platforms and software applications, mobile device and e-reader platforms, apps, social networking tools, library catalogues, photocopiers and scanners, and an ability to instruct and assist customers in the use of these tools; andKnowledge of photo, video and sound editing software, digitization equipment and software, basic desktop publishing, accessibility software, programming languages, and virtual instruction tools like video conferencing platforms would be considered an asset.The successful candidate must enjoy assisting customers on an individual basis. This position is ideally suited to someone with patience, who likes working with people of all ages, who is adaptable and can multi-task, who is calm under pressure, and who enjoys and has the ability to troubleshoot technology related questions and problems.The preferred candidate will have: a certificate or diploma in Library studies or computer information technology or systems; and open availability, particularly on Sundays and Mondays. Proficiency in Farsi or Mandarin will be considered an asset.Please include your availability in a cover letter or resume. The successful candidate will be required to supply a police information check and a copy of their credentials.This posting does not list all the duties of the position, nor does it fully detail the required skills, knowledge and abilities, licenses and certificates required of candidates. For details please refer to the Class Specification which is available for inspection in the Human Resources Department or on Westnet.Position Status:Union (WVMEA) – Casual Hours of Work:Hours and days of work may vary (less than 19 hours per week)Starting Rate of Pay:$29.20 per hour plus 14% in lieu of benefits(This position has a pay structure with five steps which increase after certain hours.)Closing Date:11:59 p.m. on Sunday October 20, 2024To Apply:Please visit the District of West Vancouver’s Career Centre at westvancouver.ca/careers to apply for this position.We want to thank all applicants, however only those chosen for an interview will be contacted. Compensation $29.20 per hour plus 14% in lieu of benefits Closes: 20 October, 2024 West Vancouver Memorial Library West Vancouver , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
