lic and staff in the use of the catalogue and the library's other online resourcesDeliver training to library staff Provide coverage for Branch Assistants when required, undertaking those duties including circulation, administration, readers' advisory / reference, and programmingPromote reading and lifelong learning in the communityRepresent the library effectively in the communityInteract pleasantly and courteously with the public, community partners and staff, promoting a harmonious workplaceProvide instructions or assistance to the public in the use of new technologies and / or electronic platformsEnsure the effective use of the Integrated Library System (ILS)Develop an understanding of electronic platforms and resources that can be used by patrons to enhance their library experienceMaintain necessary corporate files in accordance with the County of Lambton's Records Retention By-law May be required to travel to various facilities for purposes of employmentIncumbents must keep up-to-date on all relevant legislation, collective bargaining agreements, County Policies and Procedures, etc. ensuring that these are implemented as prescribed Incumbents must possess the physical ability to meet the duties and responsibilities of the job description and/or the requirements identified within the position's Physical Demands Analysis Two-Year College Library Technician Diploma or the equivalent in combination of education and experience Minimum six months in a service related job or previous volunteer work in a Library. Preference given to those who have worked in a library Computer experience including Microsoft Office products, Outlook, Internet, electronic database, digital platforms, etc. Interpersonal, communication, and customer service skills Previous library experience, and experience using an Integrated Library System (ILS) an assetA satisfactory Police Vulnerable Sector Check and / or Police Information Check, as applicable Customer Service / Communication Responsibilities: Other Job Tasks / Responsibilities: General: These describe the general nature and level of work being performed by incumbents in this classification. They are not an exhaustive list of all job duties in the classification. Other duties may be assigned. Supervision Requirements Direct Supervision: None Indirect Supervision: None Functional Authority: Regularly provide guidance and instruction to Branch Assistants, Student Pages, Summer Students, and Volunteers Credentials Required Minimum Formal Education Experience Credentials Please visit our job board at www.lambtononline.ca/jobs and search for posting LIBRA005026 to apply. Posting closes at 11:59 pm on Sunday, October 6, 2024. Compensation $27.70 Closes: 6 October, 2024 The Corporation of the County of Lambton Wyoming , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
